-- Qatar's Masraf Al Rayan Q2 profit rises 12.1 pct
-- By Olzhas Auyezov
-- Tue Jul 22, 2014 12:50AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, July 22 (Reuters) - Masraf Al Rayan <MARK.QA>, Qatar's largest Islamic lender by market value, reported a 12.1 percent increase in second-quarter net profit on Tuesday, beating analysts' expectations.

Net profit for the three months to June 30 was 471.6 million Qatar riyals ($129.5 million) compared to 420.6 million riyals in the same period a year ago, Reuters calculated based on its first-half financial statement. Analysts polled by Reuters had on average forecast a net profit of 442.3 million riyals for the period. [ID:nL6N0PI1EL]